parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the DRL can reduce visibility, posing a safety risk to the driver and other road users, especially in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The driver-side daytime running light is out
sudden failure without any prior indication.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rear Taillight Water Intrusion and Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water intrusion into the taillights can cause electrical shorts, leading to unpredictable and potentially hazardous lighting behavior, reducing the vehicle's visibility to other drivers at night.
symptoms: random flashing or complete failure of the taillights

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improperly adjusted or malfunctioning headlights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, while an overly bright backup camera can be a distraction and safety hazard.
symptoms: not providing enough lit view of the road at night
backup camera excessively bright at night

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Water Accumulation in Rear Light Bar
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Water accumulation in the rear light bar can cause LED flickering or failure, leading to reduced visibility and increased risk of accidents, especially at night.
symptoms: Water accumulation in the rear light bar

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: False or unnecessary forward collision warnings can cause distraction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Forward collision warning system activates without an obstacle

Uconnect system failure can cause distraction, leading to accidents or near-misses.
Intermittent electrical problems can cause unexpected vehicle behavior, leading to accidents or loss of control.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Parts Distribution Disconnect and Delayed Recall Repairs
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The delay in receiving recall repair parts can lead to prolonged exposure to safety risks, compromising the safety of drivers and passengers.
